cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR

The paper proposes a new convolutional neural network architecture for driver/passenger pose estimation and seat belt detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the validation of the proposed architecture on a new dataset, which involves data collection and analysis, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper addresses the detection performance under different conditions, which may be of interest to the cybersecurity (cs.CR) sub-category.
